Most of Bede’s theologica] works are dedicated to Acca, bishop of Hexham2, for whom he evidently cherished a warm affection3 3 and as Acca did not become bishop till 709, these Works cannot be earlier than that year. The latest of his purely theologica] works would seem to be the Retractations on the Acts, as it is not mentioned

in the list of Bede’s works at the end of the Ecclesiastical History written in 731 4.
